title.rendered: West Indies vs England, Women’s T20 World Cup, 2023: Fantasy Team, Probable Playing XI, Pitch Report & Fantasy Tips for the Match

content.rendered:
We have opted for a fantasy cricket team based on the recent performances, overall impact, and credit points.

Probable Playing XIs for West Indies & England

West Indies: Hayley Matthews (c), Rashada Williams (wk), Shemaine Campbelle, Stafanie Taylor, Djenaba Joseph, Aaliyah Alleyne, Afy Fletcher, Shabika Gajnabi, Chinelle Henry, Shamilia Connell, Shakera Selman/Trishan Holder

England: Sophia Dunkley, Danielle Wyatt, Natalie Sciver, Heather Knight (c), Amy Jones(wk), Maia Bouchier, Katherine Brunt, Sophie Ecclestone, Charlotte Dean, Kate Cross, Freya Davies

Venue: Boland Park, Paarl

Pitch Report for West Indies vs England, Women’s T20 World Cup, 2023

(Based on the last three games)

1st innings average score: 112

2nd innings average score: 126

Wickets per innings: 7

Type: On the slower side

Wins

Batting 1st: 67%

Batting 2nd: 33%

Also Read:

India vs Pakistan, Women’s T20 World Cup 2023 Fantasy Tips

Australia vs New Zealand, Women’s T20 World Cup 2023 Fantasy Tips

South Africa vs Sri Lanka, Women’s T20 World Cup 2023 Fantasy Tips

Fantasy Tips of The Day

Natalie Sciver and Danielle Wyatt are the leading run-getters for England against West Indies. While Sciver has added 329 runs at 25 including the highest score of 82, Wyatt has collected 307 runs at 21 including the highest score of 81.

On the bowling front, Katherine Brunt (19) and Sophie Ecclestone (15) have taken the most wickets for England against West Indies.

When these teams last crossed paths, Freya Davies (3 for 2) and Charlie Dean (2 for 8) were the power players for the game.

In only 4 games against West Indies, Dean has bagged 11 wickets.

For West Indies, Stafanie Taylor has scored the most runs (429 at 31) against England. She has also picked 23 wickets in 19 games.

After 14 games, Hayley Matthews averages only 9.57 with the bat against England but has made amends by picking 12 wickets including the best figures of 3 for 15.

In the last three games at Boland Park, 6 batters have registered scores above 30, including three half-centuries.
